          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Spallation reaction in a mercury target",
                "irradiated with 3-GeV protons (606kW).",
                "The proton beams were supplied at a repetition rate of",
                "25 Hz and in the \"double-bunch mode\", in which the",
                "pulsed protons consist of two bunches, each with a",
                "width of 100 ns, at intervals of 600 ns.",
                "To improve neutron energy resolution, Fe neutron",
                "filters with thickness of 20 cm were installed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 330 mm (diam.) and 203 mm in thickness, 90 deg",
                " with respect to the neutron beam line.",
                "Dead time is typically 3 us."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two plastic scintillator to eliminate events",
                " triggered mainly by cosmic rays:",
                " - 403 (354) mm in outer (inner) diam. and 330 mm in",
                "   length for 90deg detector;",
                " - 266 (225) mm in outer (inner) diam. and 254 mm in",
                "   length for 125deg detector.",
                "DAQ: CAEN V1720 Digitizer (12bit, 250MHz)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FNB",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron TOF experiment with a neutron",
                "filtering system."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "An 243Am sample with a mass of 38.14 mg and an",
                "activity of 281.8 MBq was used. The sample was shaped",
                "like a disk with 10 mm in diameter and 0.5 mm in",
                "thickness, made of AmO2 powder mixed with binder",
                "material of Y2O3 (39 mg) . The sample was sealed in",
                "an Al container.",
                "A dummy sample, an Al container with the identical",
                "dimensions to the 243Am sample, including only Y2O3,",
                "was also used for background measurements.",
                "A carbon sample with a diameter of 10 mm and a",
                "thickness of 0.5 mm was used as neutron scatterer",
                "to subtract background.",
                "A gold sample with a 10 mm diameter, 1 mm thickness",
                "was used for normalization.",
                "A boron sample with a diameter of 10 mm and a",
                "thickness of 0.5 mm was used for neutron spectrum",
                "measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Relative neutron TOF spectrum was measured by",
                "detecting the 478-keV gamma rays from",
                "10B(n,alpha gamma)7Li reactions.",
                "Energy distribution of the filtered neutron spectrum",
                "was written in NIM-A1003(2021)165318."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The pulse height weighting technique (PHWT) was",
                "applied to derive the neutron capture yield.",
                "Measurements with the carbon sample,",
                "\"Dummy replica sample\", and \"Blank (no sample) \" were",
                "used for back ground estimation.",
                "The neutron capture cross section of 243Am was",
                "determined relative to the capture cross section of",
                "197Au."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Dead Time Correction was applied with the extended",
                "dead-time model.",
                "Correction factors for self shielding and multiple",
                "scattering were deduced using the PHITS.",
                "Contributions of discriminated gamma-rays to the",
                "capture yields were estimated from theoretical",
                "calculation using the nuclear reaction model code",
                "CCONE and detector response functions obtained",
                "by PHITS code.",
                "Contributions from the impurities to the capture",
                "yield were calculated using the evaluated cross",
                "sections of the impurities in JENDL-4.0.",
                "The influence of the fission events was very small",
                "and neglected."
              ]
            }
          ],
